Female driver in a Toyota Aygo pulled in front of Colin Kay on the A586 in Great Eccleston in Lancashire last year . 
  Mr Kay captured the collision on a dashcam and said he had no time to react . 
  The 72-year-old was left with bruises and his wife suffered a shoulder injury . 
  But the investigating officer went off sick and will not face prosecution . 
  He has taken his case to the Independent Police Complaints Commission . 
 